d Punic War'>Second Punic War</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan='2' style='text-align:center;border-bottom:1px solid #aaa;line-height:1.5em;'><a href='/wiki/File:Battles_second_punic_war.png' class='image'><img alt='Battles second punic war.png' src='//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/Battles_second_punic_war.png/300px-Battles_second_punic_war.png' width='300' height='165' srcset='//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/Battles_second_punic_war.png/450px-Battles_second_punic_war.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2e/Battles_second_punic_war.png 2x' data-file-width='525' data-file-height='288' /></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan='2'><table style='width:100%;margin:0;padding:0;border:0'><tr><th style='padding-right:1em'>Date</th><td>208 BC</td></tr><tr><th style='padding-right:1em'>Location</th><td><span class='location'>Baecula (<a href='/wiki/Santo_Tom%C3%A9,_Ja%C3%A9n' class='mw-redirect' title='Santo Tomé, Jaén'>Santo Tomé, Jaén</a>), present-day <a href='/wiki/Spain' title='Spain'>Spain</a></span></td></tr><tr><th style='padding-right:1em'>Result</th><td>Roman victory; Hasdrubal departed Iberia without sufficient force to march on Italy immediately</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><th colspan='2' style='background-color:#B0C4DE;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle;font-size:110%;'>Belligerents</th></tr><tr><td style='width:50%;border-right:1px dotted #aaa;'><a href='/wiki/File:Carthage_standard.svg' class='image'><img alt='Carthage standard.svg' src='//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Carthage_standard.svg/12px-Carthage_standard.svg.png' width='12' height='29' srcset='//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Carthage_standard.svg/18px-Carthage_standard.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Carthage_standard.svg/24px-Carthage_standard.svg.png 2x' data-file-width='210' data-file-height='503' /></a><a href='/wiki/Ancient_Carthage' title='Ancient Carthage'>Carthage</a></td>